<h1 class="highlight">Element with Class Selector</h1>
<p>Next type of combination of selectors is the child selector. And its syntax is pretty straightforward. It's a selector, followed by a right-angle bracket, followed by another selector. And the way you read these combinations is from right to left.</p>
<p class="highlight">This is p tag with CLASS="highlight"</p>
<div class="mainpoint highlight">This is the main point of the entire article.
</div>

